  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Re https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/token/StandardToken.sol \r\n\r\nThe [standard](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20) maintains many of its methods need to return a `bool success`, e.g.\r\n```\r\nfunction transfer(address _to, uint256 _value) returns (bool success)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, the current implementation of StandardToken throws instead of ever returning `false`.\r\nWhile there is an ongoing debate on the standards page about return vs. throw, don't you think existing contracts should conform to the `return` paradigm for now?",
